Oopsie doopsie! I missed a day of this, yesterday was a bit... difficult.

But anyway, onto day 11: Where do you work on cosplays, and where do you store them after?

Well, in the photos are my work areas, please pardon the mess >.> But my grandpa did make an area for me when i first moved in. Under my sewing machine is my grandmas antique one, next to it is a storing drawer, and next to the machine is my drawing desk which it covered in filth xp

Where i store them is a work in progress. I have limited areas to store them, so they actually take up one entire side of my closet. Which is not safe. I still don't know where to store Zeldas armor tbh. I just don't have the space in my tiny room.

There are all sorts of organisational gems you can include in a custom vanity so it's an option worth investigating. This vanity also includes a small pull-out bin, and had the vanity been floorstanding rather than wall hung, I could have also fit a pull out laundry hamper.  But there's always a line between functional and ugly, and the wall-hung design gives a sense of lightness and space to the room that was preferable to a built in laundry basket.
